place.name: WEST BECKHAM
place.gazetteerText: BECKHAM (West), a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; 5 miles WSW of Cromer, and 13 E by N of Walsingham r. station. Post Town, Lower Sherringham, under Norwich. Acres, 785. Real property, £1,477. Pop., 32 9. Houses, 42. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £61. Patrons, the Dean and Chapter of Norwich. The church is early English, and had formerly a round tower, surmounted by an octagonal lanthern. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
